



How to use gcc 5.x on ubuntu 14.04  OR HIGHER VERSIONS FOR Ubuntu 20.04





RUN THE INSTALLATION PROCESS:



sudo add-apt-repository ppa:ubuntu-toolchain-r/test

sudo apt-get update

sudo apt-get install gcc-5 g++-5



sudo update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/gcc gcc /usr/bin/gcc-5 60 --slave /usr/bin/g++ g++ /usr/bin/g++-5





sudo update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/gcc gcc /usr/bin/gcc-5 1



to set first priority to gcc-5











root@a8d5b4cdb27b:/# sudo apt-get install gcc-5 g++-5

Reading package lists... Done

Building dependency tree

Reading state information... Done

Package g++-5 is not available, but is referred to by another package.

This may mean that the package is missing, has been obsoleted, or

is only available from another source





However the following packages replace it:

  gcc-10-test-results gcc-11-test-results gcc-9-test-results gcc-8-test-results gcc-7-test-results
  




TO GCC a (dot c file i.e .c file  Take for example main.c) below is the format:



gcc -o nameofOutput nameofInput.c



congratulations.

